cntSysNodeAddress.name: cntSysNodeAddress
cntSysNodeAddress.description: Node address of this CNT platform. This value contains the region (1 byte), the bus (1 byte), and the node (2 bytes).

cntSysTimeofDay.name: cntSysTimeofDay
cntSysTimeofDay.description: The date and time from Battery-Backed-up RAM (BBRAM).

cntSysMsgTable.name: cntSysMsgTable
cntSysMsgTable.description: List of entries in the global mail box. This mail box contains any message that have been entered by any software residing in the node.

cntMsgIndex.name: cntMsgIndex
cntMsgIndex.description: The relative index of this mail box message.

cntMsgSeverity.name: cntMsgSeverity
cntMsgSeverity.description: The severity of this mail box message.

cntMsgTaskName.name: cntMsgTaskName
cntMsgTaskName.description: The name of the module that sent this message to the mail box.

cntMsgNumber.name: cntMsgNumber
cntMsgNumber.description: The number of this message. Each module numbers its message type as another way of describing it. This message can then be cross-referenced in the CNT system messages reference manual.

cntMsgCpuNumber.name: cntMsgCpuNumber
cntMsgCpuNumber.description: The CPU of the module that sent this message to the mail box.

cntMsgNodeNumber.name: cntMsgNodeNumber
cntMsgNodeNumber.description: The node number of the module that sent this message to the mail box.

cntMsgDateTime.name: cntMsgDateTime
cntMsgDateTime.description: The date and time that this message was sent to the mail box.

cntMsgContent.name: cntMsgContent
cntMsgContent.description: The textual contents of the message sent to the mail box.

cntMsgSeqNumber.name: cntMsgSeqNumber
cntMsgSeqNumber.description: The sequence number for this message.

cntHwBBramType.name: cntHwBBramType
cntHwBBramType.description: The type of battery backed up memory.

cntHwBBramStatus.name: cntHwBBramStatus
cntHwBBramStatus.description: The status of the batteries used in the BBRAM. A failing status indicates that one or more of the batteries are failing.

cntHwFailedCpu.name: cntHwFailedCpu
cntHwFailedCpu.description: The CPU number where a failure occurred. If this value is zero then there are no failures.

cntHwMonCpu.name: cntHwMonCpu
cntHwMonCpu.description: The CPU number of the monitor that noticed the CPU failure.

cntHwFailStatus.name: cntHwFailStatus
cntHwFailStatus.description: Status that the failing CPU recorded at the time of the failure.

cntHwMonFailStatus.name: cntHwMonFailStatus
cntHwMonFailStatus.description: Status that the monitoring CPU recorded at the time of the failure.

cntHwFailDate.name: cntHwFailDate
cntHwFailDate.description: Time and date when the processor failed.

cntHwReset1Why.name: cntHwReset1Why
cntHwReset1Why.description: The reason for the last reset.

cntHwReset1Date.name: cntHwReset1Date
cntHwReset1Date.description: The time and date of the last reset.

cntHwReset2Why.name: cntHwReset2Why
cntHwReset2Why.description: The reason for the second-to-last reset.

cntHwReset2Date.name: cntHwReset2Date
cntHwReset2Date.description: The time and date of the second-to-last reset.

cntHwReset3Why.name: cntHwReset3Why
cntHwReset3Why.description: The reason for the third-to-last reset.

cntHwReset3Date.name: cntHwReset3Date
cntHwReset3Date.description: The time and date of the third-to-last reset.

cntHwPowerSupply.name: cntHwPowerSupply
cntHwPowerSupply.description: The status of the power supply or power supplies. This value will indicate good only if all power supplies in the node are working. If any fan or power supply is failing, this object will indicate a failure even if enough power is supplied to keep the node operating.

cntHwCpuTable.name: cntHwCpuTable
cntHwCpuTable.description: A list of CPU statistics entries. All possible CPUs for a box are accessible whether or not they even exist.

cntCpuType.name: cntCpuType
cntCpuType.description: The type of the CPU requested.

cntCpuSemCount.name: cntCpuSemCount
cntCpuSemCount.description: The number of semaphores for this CPU.

cntCpuSemLost.name: cntCpuSemLost
cntCpuSemLost.description: The number of semaphores lost for this CPU.

cntCpuStatus.name: cntCpuStatus
cntCpuStatus.description: The current known status of this CPU.

cntCpuMonStatus.name: cntCpuMonStatus
cntCpuMonStatus.description: The current status of this CPU as known by the monitoring CPU.

cntCpuPollStatus.name: cntCpuPollStatus
cntCpuPollStatus.description: The status of the current polling request for this CPU.

cntCpuPolls.name: cntCpuPolls
cntCpuPolls.description: The number of polls sent for this CPU.

cntCpuResetDelayTime.name: cntCpuResetDelayTime
cntCpuResetDelayTime.description: The reset delay time, in seconds.

cntCpuMonBy.name: cntCpuMonBy
cntCpuMonBy.description: The system number for the CPU monitoring this CPU.

cntCpuPort.name: cntCpuPort
cntCpuPort.description: The port number for this CPU.

cntCpuUnclaims.name: cntCpuUnclaims
cntCpuUnclaims.description: The number of unclaimed grant interrupts on the system controller CPU.

cntCpuLevel7s.name: cntCpuLevel7s
cntCpuLevel7s.description: The number of unidentified level seven interrupts.

cntCpuMsgRets.name: cntCpuMsgRets
cntCpuMsgRets.description: The number of undeliverable MDM interprocessor messages.

cntCpuMsgHolds.name: cntCpuMsgHolds
cntCpuMsgHolds.description: The number of messages held which were being returned to the failed processor.

cntCpuResetFlag.name: cntCpuResetFlag
cntCpuResetFlag.description: The value of the reset flag.

cntCpuUtil.name: cntCpuUtil
cntCpuUtil.description: The CPU utilization, in percent utilized.

cntCpuLastFailDate.name: cntCpuLastFailDate
cntCpuLastFailDate.description: The date and time of the last failure.

cntCpuLastChgDate.name: cntCpuLastChgDate
cntCpuLastChgDate.description: The date and time of the last change.

cntHwStatusLED.name: cntHwStatusLED
cntHwStatusLED.description: Two digit, LCD display. During system initialization it indicates the processor that is being initialized. Successful initialization is indicated by a display of '00'.

cntRevDate.name: cntRevDate
cntRevDate.description: The BBRAM revision date of the system description (!RV2) file.

cntCustomer.name: cntCustomer
cntCustomer.description: Customer name and other identifying information.

cntMachineType.name: cntMachineType
cntMachineType.description: The machine type of this node.

cntSerialNumber.name: cntSerialNumber
cntSerialNumber.description: The machine serial number of this node.

cntWorkOrderNumber.name: cntWorkOrderNumber
cntWorkOrderNumber.description: The original manufacturing build work order number of this node.

cntChassisNumber.name: cntChassisNumber
cntChassisNumber.description: The machine chassis number of this node.

cntModelNumber.name: cntModelNumber
cntModelNumber.description: The machine model number of this node.

cntReleaseLevel.name: cntReleaseLevel
cntReleaseLevel.description: The original software release level installed in this node.

cntRevEditDate.name: cntRevEditDate
cntRevEditDate.description: The date that this version of the system description (!RV2) file was edited dynamically.

cntRevEditTime.name: cntRevEditTime
cntRevEditTime.description: The time that this version of the system description (!RV2) file was edited dynamically.

cntFeatureTable.name: cntFeatureTable
cntFeatureTable.description: The list of manufacturing features originally installed in this node.

cntSlotTable.name: cntSlotTable
cntSlotTable.description: The list of VME slots in this node.

cntSlotName.name: cntSlotName
cntSlotName.description: The board name in this slot.

cntSlotPartNumber.name: cntSlotPartNumber
cntSlotPartNumber.description: The part number for the board in this slot.

cntSlotSerialNumber.name: cntSlotSerialNumber
cntSlotSerialNumber.description: The serial number for the board in this slot.

cntSlotRevLevel.name: cntSlotRevLevel
cntSlotRevLevel.description: The revision number of the board in this slot.

cntSlotInterface.name: cntSlotInterface
cntSlotInterface.description: The interface name of the board in this slot.

cntSlotCpuNumber.name: cntSlotCpuNumber
cntSlotCpuNumber.description: The cpu number of the board in this slot.

cntSlotVMEbusGrant.name: cntSlotVMEbusGrant
cntSlotVMEbusGrant.description: The VME bus grant priority of the board in this slot.

cntIOTable.name: cntIOTable
cntIOTable.description: The list of VME I/O boards in this node.

cntIOPartNumber.name: cntIOPartNumber
cntIOPartNumber.description: The part number for this I/O board.

cntIOSerialNumber.name: cntIOSerialNumber
cntIOSerialNumber.description: The serial number for this I/O board.

cntIORevLevel.name: cntIORevLevel
cntIORevLevel.description: The revision number of this I/O board.

cntIOInterface.name: cntIOInterface
cntIOInterface.description: The interface name of this I/O board.

cntIOCpuNumber.name: cntIOCpuNumber
cntIOCpuNumber.description: The cpu number of this I/O board.

cntPowerTable.name: cntPowerTable
cntPowerTable.description: The list of power supplies in this node.

cntPowerPartNumber.name: cntPowerPartNumber
cntPowerPartNumber.description: The part number for this power supply.

cntPowerSerialNumber.name: cntPowerSerialNumber
cntPowerSerialNumber.description: The serial number for this power supply.

cntPowerRevLevel.name: cntPowerRevLevel
cntPowerRevLevel.description: The revision number of this power supply.

cntSCRTable.name: cntSCRTable
cntSCRTable.description: The list of SCRs in this node.

cntSCRNumber.name: cntSCRNumber
cntSCRNumber.description: A SCR number installed in this node.

cntSerialAlfaNumber.name: cntSerialAlfaNumber
cntSerialAlfaNumber.description: The machine serial number of this node.

cntMemBBramAddress.name: cntMemBBramAddress
cntMemBBramAddress.description: The starting address of battery-backed-up RAM. BBRAM is used to store the software and configuration files.

cntMemBBramSpace.name: cntMemBBramSpace
cntMemBBramSpace.description: The amount of BBRAM memory in bytes installed in this node.

cntMemBBramFree.name: cntMemBBramFree
cntMemBBramFree.description: The amount of BBRAM memory in bytes available in this node.

cntMemSramAddress.name: cntMemSramAddress
cntMemSramAddress.description: The starting address of static ram. SRAM is used as buffer space.

cntMemSramSpace.name: cntMemSramSpace
cntMemSramSpace.description: The amount of SRAM memory in bytes installed in this node.

cntMemSramFree.name: cntMemSramFree
cntMemSramFree.description: The amount of SRAM memory in bytes available in this node.

cntCpuMemSpace.name: cntCpuMemSpace
cntCpuMemSpace.description: The amount of memory in bytes installed in this cpu.

cntCpuMemFree.name: cntCpuMemFree
cntCpuMemFree.description: The amount of memory in bytes available in this cpu.

cntCpuTaskIndex.name: cntCpuTaskIndex
cntCpuTaskIndex.description: The relative index of the task on this cpu.

cntCpuTaskName.name: cntCpuTaskName
cntCpuTaskName.description: The operating system name for a loaded and possibly executing task on this cpu.

cntifTable.name: cntifTable
cntifTable.description: A list of CNT interface entries.

cntifIndex.name: cntifIndex
cntifIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface on a CNT node. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of IfIndex.

cntifType.name: cntifType
cntifType.description: The type of interface. For standardized interface types in mib-2, this number is redundant. CNT specific interface types are appended to the end of the standardized list.

cntifCpu.name: cntifCpu
cntifCpu.description: The cpu number where the device driver for this interface resides.

cntifSubIndex.name: cntifSubIndex
cntifSubIndex.description: A value that uniquely indexes an interface in a multiply-interfaced device driver.

cntIfsState.name: cntIfsState
cntIfsState.description: A 32 bit-map of the interface states. The bits are ordered from 1 to 32 with the most significant bit on the left. if the bit is set, the corresponding interface is up. if the bit is clear, the interface is not up - down or in test mode.

cnticmpInDuNets.name: cnticmpInDuNets
cnticmpInDuNets.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received for an unreachable network.

cnticmpInDuHosts.name: cnticmpInDuHosts
cnticmpInDuHosts.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received for an unreachable host.

cnticmpInDuProtos.name: cnticmpInDuProtos
cnticmpInDuProtos.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received due to an unreachable protocol.

cnticmpInDuPorts.name: cnticmpInDuPorts
cnticmpInDuPorts.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received due to an unreachable port.

cnticmpInDuFrags.name: cnticmpInDuFrags
cnticmpInDuFrags.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received due to a fragmentation requirement but the Don't Fragment flag is set.

cnticmpInDuSources.name: cnticmpInDuSources
cnticmpInDuSources.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was received due to a source route that is not usable.

cnticmpInTmXceeds.name: cnticmpInTmXceeds
cnticmpInTmXceeds.description: The number of times a time exceeded message was received for an expired datagram.

cnticmpInTmFrags.name: cnticmpInTmFrags
cnticmpInTmFrags.description: The number of times a time exceeded message was received for a datagram that could not be reassembled before its lifetime expired.

cnticmpInReNets.name: cnticmpInReNets
cnticmpInReNets.description: The number of times a redirect message was received due to a shorter path to a destination network having been found.

cnticmpInReHosts.name: cnticmpInReHosts
cnticmpInReHosts.description: The number of times a redirect message was received due to a shorter path to a destination host having been found.

cnticmpInReServnets.name: cnticmpInReServnets
cnticmpInReServnets.description: The number of times a redirect message was received due to a shorter path to a destination network with the requested type of service having been found.

cnticmpInReServhosts.name: cnticmpInReServhosts
cnticmpInReServhosts.description: The number of times a redirect message was received due to a shorter path to a destination host with the requested type of service having been found.

cnticmpOutDuNets.name: cnticmpOutDuNets
cnticmpOutDuNets.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent to a requester when it attempted to send a datagram to an unreachable network.

cnticmpOutDuHosts.name: cnticmpOutDuHosts
cnticmpOutDuHosts.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent to a requester when it attempted to send a datagram to an unreachable host.

cnticmpOutDuProtos.name: cnticmpOutDuProtos
cnticmpOutDuProtos.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent to a requester when it attempted to send a datagram to an unreachable protocol.

cnticmpOutDuPorts.name: cnticmpOutDuPorts
cnticmpOutDuPorts.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent to a requester when it attempted to send a datagram to an unreachable port.

cnticmpOutDuFrags.name: cnticmpOutDuFrags
cnticmpOutDuFrags.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent to a requester when it attempted to send a datagram requiring fragmentation but the Don't Fragment flag is set.

cnticmpOutDuSources.name: cnticmpOutDuSources
cnticmpOutDuSources.description: The number of times a destination unreachable message was sent due to a source route that is not usable.

cnticmpOutTmXceeds.name: cnticmpOutTmXceeds
cnticmpOutTmXceeds.description: The number of times a time exceeded message was sent for an expired datagram.

cnticmpOutTmFrags.name: cnticmpOutTmFrags
cnticmpOutTmFrags.description: The number of times a time exceeded message was sent for a datagram that could not be reassembled before its lifetime expired.

cnticmpOutReNets.name: cnticmpOutReNets
cnticmpOutReNets.description: The number of times a redirect message was sent due to a shorter path to a destination network having been found.

cnticmpOutReHosts.name: cnticmpOutReHosts
cnticmpOutReHosts.description: The number of times a redirect message was sent due to a shorter path to a destination host having been found.

cnticmpOutReServnets.name: cnticmpOutReServnets
cnticmpOutReServnets.description: The number of times a redirect message was sent due to a shorter path to a destination network with the requested type of service having been found.

cnticmpOutReServhosts.name: cnticmpOutReServhosts
cnticmpOutReServhosts.description: The number of times a redirect message was sent due to a shorter path to a destination host with the requested type of service having been found.

cntdot3Table.name: cntdot3Table
cntdot3Table.description: Status information and control variables for a collection of ethernet software device drivers in a particular CNT system.

cntdot3Entry.name: cntdot3Entry
cntdot3Entry.description: Status information and control variables for a particular CNT ethernet software device driver.

cntdot3Index.name: cntdot3Index
cntdot3Index.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to a CNT ethernet-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of IfIndex.

cntdot3SoftwareID.name: cntdot3SoftwareID
cntdot3SoftwareID.description: The binary software revision number in the header of the ethernet driver.

cntdot3BufsAllocated.name: cntdot3BufsAllocated
cntdot3BufsAllocated.description: The number of CNT buffers allocated by the ethernet device driver at initialization.

cntdot3BufTooManys.name: cntdot3BufTooManys
cntdot3BufTooManys.description: The number of buffers sent by a higher layer that were returned to that layer without transmission due to a full queue of waiting outbound buffers.

cntdot3BufNotAvails.name: cntdot3BufNotAvails
cntdot3BufNotAvails.description: The number of requests made to the free pool of ethernet buffers that failed due to a lack buffers in that pool.

cntdot3BufPriority.name: cntdot3BufPriority
cntdot3BufPriority.description: The priority value assigned to inbound ethernet buffers.

cntdot3PICBusErrs.name: cntdot3PICBusErrs
cntdot3PICBusErrs.description: The number of times a failure was detected when attempting to access the VME bus.

cntdot3PICDMAErrs.name: cntdot3PICDMAErrs
cntdot3PICDMAErrs.description: The number of times ethernet local memory had a parity error during a DMA memory cycle. These errors would normally indicate a hardware problem.

cntdot3PICMemSeqErrs.name: cntdot3PICMemSeqErrs
cntdot3PICMemSeqErrs.description: The number of times the hardware could not successfully arbitrate multiple requests to access ethernet local memory. These errors would normally indicate a hardware problem.

cntdot3PICMemParityErrs.name: cntdot3PICMemParityErrs
cntdot3PICMemParityErrs.description: The number of ethernet local memory parity errors. These errors would normally indicate a hardware problem.

cntdot3PICSpuriousInts.name: cntdot3PICSpuriousInts
cntdot3PICSpuriousInts.description: The number of interrupts generated by the PIC that were not mapped to any particular hardware event.

cntdot3LanceInts.name: cntdot3LanceInts
cntdot3LanceInts.description: The number of LANCE hardware interrupts detected by the controlling CPU.

cntdot3LanceParityErrs.name: cntdot3LanceParityErrs
cntdot3LanceParityErrs.description: The number of parity errors detected when the LANCE was accessing local memory. These errors would normally indicate a hardware problem.

cntdot3LanceMemErrs.name: cntdot3LanceMemErrs
cntdot3LanceMemErrs.description: The number of times the LANCE detected a local memory access failure.

cntdot3LanceMissedPkts.name: cntdot3LanceMissedPkts
cntdot3LanceMissedPkts.description: The number of packets on the ethernet medium that were detected by the LANCE but failed to be captured in the inbound queue.

cntdot3LanceUnderFlows.name: cntdot3LanceUnderFlows
cntdot3LanceUnderFlows.description: The number of message truncated by the LANCE transmitter due to data late from memory. An underflow indication by the LANCE indicates that the silo was emptied before the end of the packet was reached.

cntdot3LanceOverFlows.name: cntdot3LanceOverFlows
cntdot3LanceOverFlows.description: The number of times the LANCE receiver lost all or part of the incoming packet due to an inability to store the packet in a memory buffer before the internal silo overflowed.

cntdot3LanceTxWaitQ.name: cntdot3LanceTxWaitQ
cntdot3LanceTxWaitQ.description: The number of buffers in local memory and on the ethernet device driver's software queue awaiting transmission by the LANCE.

cntdot3DMAChan1RxErr.name: cntdot3DMAChan1RxErr
cntdot3DMAChan1RxErr.description: The error code reported by the DMA controller channel 1. This channel is used to write inbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan3RxErr.name: cntdot3DMAChan3RxErr
cntdot3DMAChan3RxErr.description: The error code reported by the DMA controller channel 3. This channel is used to write inbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan0TxErr.name: cntdot3DMAChan0TxErr
cntdot3DMAChan0TxErr.description: The error code reported by the DMA controller channel 0. This channel is used to write outbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan2TxErr.name: cntdot3DMAChan2TxErr
cntdot3DMAChan2TxErr.description: The error code reported by the DMA controller channel 2. This channel is used to write outbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan1RxErrs.name: cntdot3DMAChan1RxErrs
cntdot3DMAChan1RxErrs.description: The number of errors reported by the DMA controller channel 1. This channel is used to write inbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan3RxErrs.name: cntdot3DMAChan3RxErrs
cntdot3DMAChan3RxErrs.description: The number of errors reported by the DMA controller channel 1. This channel is used to write inbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan0TxErrs.name: cntdot3DMAChan0TxErrs
cntdot3DMAChan0TxErrs.description: The number of errors reported by the DMA controller channel 1. This channel is used to write outbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMAChan2TxErrs.name: cntdot3DMAChan2TxErrs
cntdot3DMAChan2TxErrs.description: The number of errors reported by the DMA controller channel 1. This channel is used to write outbound ethernet messages.

cntdot3DMARxWaitQ.name: cntdot3DMARxWaitQ
cntdot3DMARxWaitQ.description: The number of successfully received ethernet messages awaiting transmission by the DMA to global memory buffers.

cntdot3DMATxWaitQ.name: cntdot3DMATxWaitQ
cntdot3DMATxWaitQ.description: The number of buffers waiting in an outbound queue ready to transmitted to local memory from global memory. Buffers must be moved from global memory to local memory in order to be transmitted by the LANCE.

cntdot3LPXParityErrs.name: cntdot3LPXParityErrs
cntdot3LPXParityErrs.description: The number of local memory parity errors during an LPX memory cycle.

cntdot3Chan1Misreads.name: cntdot3Chan1Misreads
cntdot3Chan1Misreads.description: The number of times a mismatch was detected between the DMA channel 1 table and the DMA Memory Access Register.

cntFddiSMTNumber.name: cntFddiSMTNumber
cntFddiSMTNumber.description: The number of SMT implementations on this network management application entity.

cntFddiSMTTable.name: cntFddiSMTTable
cntFddiSMTTable.description: A list of SMT entries. The number of entries is given by the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber.

cntFddiSMTEntry.name: cntFddiSMTEntry
cntFddiSMTEntry.description: An SMT entry containing information common to a given SMT.

cntFddiSMTIndex.name: cntFddiSMTIndex
cntFddiSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber.

cntFddiSMTManufacturerData.name: cntFddiSMTManufacturerData
cntFddiSMTManufacturerData.description: 32 octets of manufacturer data. The first component is the three octet Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) assigned by IEEE. The second component is the FDDI manufacturer's data (29 octets).

cntFddiSMTReportLimit.name: cntFddiSMTReportLimit
cntFddiSMTReportLimit.description: Gives the limit on the number of Status Report Frames that shall be queued for transmission after supported Condition becomes inactive or after any supported Event has been detected.

cntFddiSMTMsgTimeStamp.name: cntFddiSMTMsgTimeStamp
cntFddiSMTMsgTimeStamp.description: This timestamp is used in some SMT frames as an indication of the time the message was created at the sending station. When read, the accessed value shall be greater than or equal to the value used in the station's last message. The timestamp may be reset whenever there is a discontinuity in the accumulation of a statistical counter.

cntFddiSMTTransitionTimeStamp.name: cntFddiSMTTransitionTimeStamp
cntFddiSMTTransitionTimeStamp.description: This timestamp holds the time of occurrence of the last condition or event in the station. It is used in the SMT Status Report Frame (SRF). It is set to a new value on each event to capture the time of the latest event occurrence. On power-up, the value of the attribute is zero.

cntFddiSMTSetCount.name: cntFddiSMTSetCount
cntFddiSMTSetCount.description: This count is updated each time a parameter is changed on behalf of a request from either the local management interface or the remote interface via SMT Parameter Management Frames. It is used to provide consistency control for MIB updates.

cntFddiSMTLastSetStationID.name: cntFddiSMTLastSetStationID
cntFddiSMTLastSetStationID.description: This object identifies the last station to set MIB information in the FDDI MIB.

cntFddiMACNumber.name: cntFddiMACNumber
cntFddiMACNumber.description: The total number of MAC implementations across all SMTs on this network management application entity.

cntFddiMACTable.name: cntFddiMACTable
cntFddiMACTable.description: A list of MAC entries. The number of entries is given by the value of snmpFddiMACNumber.

cntFddiMACEntry.name: cntFddiMACEntry
cntFddiMACEntry.description: A MAC entry containing information common to a given MAC.

cntFddiMACSMTIndex.name: cntFddiMACSMTIndex
cntFddiMACSMTIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this MAC.

cntFddiMACIndex.name: cntFddiMACIndex
cntFddiMACIndex.description: A unique value for each MAC on the managed entity. The MAC identified by a particular value of this index is that identified by the same value of an ifIndex object instance.

cntFddiMACBridgeFunction.name: cntFddiMACBridgeFunction
cntFddiMACBridgeFunction.description: Gives the bridge type for a MAC that has a bridge capability.

cntFddiMACDownstreamNbr.name: cntFddiMACDownstreamNbr
cntFddiMACDownstreamNbr.description: The MAC's downstream neighbor's long individual MAC address. It may be determined by the Neighbor Information Frame Request/ Response protocol. It is optional an reported as zero in SMT frames if unknown or unsupported.

cntFddiMACOldDownstreamNbr.name: cntFddiMACOldDownstreamNbr
cntFddiMACOldDownstreamNbr.description: This object identifies this MAC's previous downstream neighbor.

cntFddiMACRootConcentratorMac.name: cntFddiMACRootConcentratorMac
cntFddiMACRootConcentratorMac.description: A MAC in a concentrator is a root concentrator MAC if its transmit path exits the concentrator via a Port in a peer node; or if the MAC exits via a Port in a tree node and there is no A, B, or S Ports that are active on that MAC's current Path.

cntFddiMACLongAlias.name: cntFddiMACLongAlias
cntFddiMACLongAlias.description: A possibly null set of 48 bit addresses (aliases) for this MAC.

cntFddiMACShortAlias.name: cntFddiMACShortAlias
cntFddiMACShortAlias.description: A possibly null set of 16 bit addresses (aliases) for this MAC.

cntFddiMACLongGrpAddr.name: cntFddiMACLongGrpAddr
cntFddiMACLongGrpAddr.description: A possibly null set of 48 bit group addresses (aliases) for this MAC.

cntFddiMACShortGrpAddr.name: cntFddiMACShortGrpAddr
cntFddiMACShortGrpAddr.description: A possibly null set of 16 bit group addresses (aliases) for this MAC.

cntFddiMACTPri0.name: cntFddiMACTPri0
cntFddiMACTPri0.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri1.name: cntFddiMACTPri1
cntFddiMACTPri1.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri2.name: cntFddiMACTPri2
cntFddiMACTPri2.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri3.name: cntFddiMACTPri3
cntFddiMACTPri3.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri4.name: cntFddiMACTPri4
cntFddiMACTPri4.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri5.name: cntFddiMACTPri5
cntFddiMACTPri5.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACTPri6.name: cntFddiMACTPri6
cntFddiMACTPri6.description: Reference: Mac 2.2.1. It is reported as the unsigned twos-complement of the number (as described in the MAC specification; ref. MAC 7.3.5.2).

cntFddiMACCopies.name: cntFddiMACCopies
cntFddiMACCopies.description: The count of frames successfully received into the station's receive buffers by this MAC. Note that this count does not include the frames that are not copied. This counter is optional.

cntFddiMACTransmits.name: cntFddiMACTransmits
cntFddiMACTransmits.description: The count of frames transmitted by the MAC.

cntFddiMACTokens.name: cntFddiMACTokens
cntFddiMACTokens.description: The total count of the number of times the station has received a token (total of non-restricted and restricted) on this MAC. This count is used for determination of network load.

cntFddiMACTvxExpires.name: cntFddiMACTvxExpires
cntFddiMACTvxExpires.description: A count of the times that TVX expired.

cntFddiMACNotCopies.name: cntFddiMACNotCopies
cntFddiMACNotCopies.description: The count of frames that should have been copied but were not. This might occur due to local buffer congestion. Because of implementation considerations, this count may be less than the actual number of frames not copied. It is not a requirement that this count be exact.

cntFddiMACRingOps.name: cntFddiMACRingOps
cntFddiMACRingOps.description: The count of the number of times the ring has entered the 'Ring Operational' state from 'Ring Not Operational' state. Because of implementation considerations, this count may not be exact.

cntFddiMACBaseFrames.name: cntFddiMACBaseFrames
cntFddiMACBaseFrames.description: The value of FddiMACFrameCt at the sample time prior to the sample time when the FrameErrorThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset when the associated condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACBaseErrs.name: cntFddiMACBaseErrs
cntFddiMACBaseErrs.description: The value of FddiMACErrorCt at the sample time prior to the sample time when the FrameErrorThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset to the current value of the corresponding 'real' counter when the associated condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACBaseLosts.name: cntFddiMACBaseLosts
cntFddiMACBaseLosts.description: The value of FddiMACLostCt at the sample time prior to the sample time when the FrameErrorThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset to the current value of the corresponding 'real' counter when the associated condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACBaseTimeFrameError.name: cntFddiMACBaseTimeFrameError
cntFddiMACBaseTimeFrameError.description: The value of the station timer at the sample time prior to the sample time when the FrameErrorThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset when the new condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACBaseNotCopies.name: cntFddiMACBaseNotCopies
cntFddiMACBaseNotCopies.description: The value of FddiMACNotCopiedCt at the sample time prior to the sample time when the NotCopiedThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset when the new condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACBaseTimeNotCopied.name: cntFddiMACBaseTimeNotCopied
cntFddiMACBaseTimeNotCopied.description: The value of the station timer at the sample time prior to the sample time when the NotCopiedThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset when the new condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACNotCopiedThreshold.name: cntFddiMACNotCopiedThreshold
cntFddiMACNotCopiedThreshold.description: A threshold for determining when a MAC Condition report should be generated. It is used to determine when a station has an unacceptable count of frames 'not-copied'. It could be used as an indication of buffer congestion on this MAC.

cntFddiMACBaseCopies.name: cntFddiMACBaseCopies
cntFddiMACBaseCopies.description: The value of FddiMACCopiedCt at the sample time prior to the sample time when the NotCopiedThreshold was reached. It is used in reporting the condition to give the manager the necessary data to reconstruct the condition at the station. Reset when the new condition becomes active.

cntFddiMACNotCopiedRatio.name: cntFddiMACNotCopiedRatio
cntFddiMACNotCopiedRatio.description: This attribute is the value of the ratio: FddiMACNotCopiedCt ----------------------------------- * (2 ** 16) FddiMACCopiedCt + FddiMACNotCopiedCt

cntFddiMACNotCopiedCondition.name: cntFddiMACNotCopiedCondition
cntFddiMACNotCopiedCondition.description: Indicates the NotCopiedCondition is active when set. Cleared when the condition clears and on power up.

cntFddiMACLLCServiceAvailable.name: cntFddiMACLLCServiceAvailable
cntFddiMACLLCServiceAvailable.description: Indicates whether the LLC Service is enabled.

cntFddiMACMasterSlaveLoopStatus.name: cntFddiMACMasterSlaveLoopStatus
cntFddiMACMasterSlaveLoopStatus.description: Indicates this MAC's Master/Slave Loop Status. This status would be obtained with the Root MAC Information Protocol.

cntFddiMACRootMACDownStreamPORTType.name: cntFddiMACRootMACDownStreamPORTType
cntFddiMACRootMACDownStreamPORTType.description: Indicates the PC-Type of the first PORT that is downstream of the Root MAC associated with this MAC. The Root MAC information would be determined in the Root MAC Information Protocol.

cntFddiMACRootMACCurrentPath.name: cntFddiMACRootMACCurrentPath
cntFddiMACRootMACCurrentPath.description: Indicates the current path of the Root MAC on the same logical ring as this MAC. This Root MAC information would be determined in the Root MAC Information Protocol.

cntFddiPATHNumber.name: cntFddiPATHNumber
cntFddiPATHNumber.description: The total number of PATH implementations across all SMTs on this network management application entity.

cntFddiPATHTable.name: cntFddiPATHTable
cntFddiPATHTable.description: A list of PATH entries. The number of entries is given by the value of snmpFddiPATHNumber.

cntFddiPATHEntry.name: cntFddiPATHEntry
cntFddiPATHEntry.description: A PATH entry containing information common to a given PATH.

cntFddiPATHSMTIndex.name: cntFddiPATHSMTIndex
cntFddiPATHSMTIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this PATH.

cntFddiPATHIndex.name: cntFddiPATHIndex
cntFddiPATHIndex.description: A unique value for each PATH within a given SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the sum of the values of snmpFddiSMTNonMasterCt and snmpFddiSMTMasterCt on the given SMT.

cntFddiPATHTVXLowerBound.name: cntFddiPATHTVXLowerBound
cntFddiPATHTVXLowerBound.description: The lower bound of TVX supported for this PATH.

cntFddiPATHTMaxLowerBound.name: cntFddiPATHTMaxLowerBound
cntFddiPATHTMaxLowerBound.description: The lower bound of TMax supported for this PATH class.

cntFddiPATHType.name: cntFddiPATHType
cntFddiPATHType.description: This object describes the type of PATH: 1 = Primary, 2 = Secondary, 3 = Local.

cntFddiPATHPORTOrder.name: cntFddiPATHPORTOrder
cntFddiPATHPORTOrder.description: Tells whether the PORTs on this path are numbered in ascending of descending order.

cntFddiPATHRingLatency.name: cntFddiPATHRingLatency
cntFddiPATHRingLatency.description: Gives the total accumulated latency of the ring associated with this PATH. May be measured directly by the station or may be calculated by a management station.

cntFddiPATHTraceStatus.name: cntFddiPATHTraceStatus
cntFddiPATHTraceStatus.description: Gives the current trace status of the PATH.

cntFddiPATHSba.name: cntFddiPATHSba
cntFddiPATHSba.description: The Synchronous Bandwidth Allocation for this PATH within the station in octet units. In stations that don't support synchronous service, this attribute is read only and has the value of 0.

cntFddiPATHSbaOverhead.name: cntFddiPATHSbaOverhead
cntFddiPATHSbaOverhead.description: The Synchronous Bandwidth Allocation overhead for this PATH (bytes/frame). In stations that don't support synchronous service, this attribute is read only and has the value of 0.

cntFddiPATHStatus.name: cntFddiPATHStatus
cntFddiPATHStatus.description: The current status of the PATH.

cntFddiPATHTRmode.name: cntFddiPATHTRmode
cntFddiPATHTRmode.description: Used by RMT to limit the duration of restricted dialogs on a PATH.

cntFddiPORTNumber.name: cntFddiPORTNumber
cntFddiPORTNumber.description: The total number of PORT implementations across all SMTs on this network management application entity.

cntFddiPORTTable.name: cntFddiPORTTable
cntFddiPORTTable.description: A list of PORT entries. The number of entries is given by the value of snmpFddiPORTNumber.

cntFddiPORTEntry.name: cntFddiPORTEntry
cntFddiPORTEntry.description: A PORT entry containing information common to a given PORT.

cntFddiPORTSMTIndex.name: cntFddiPORTSMTIndex
cntFddiPORTSMTIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this PORT.

cntFddiPORTIndex.name: cntFddiPORTIndex
cntFddiPORTIndex.description: A unique value for each PORT within a given SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the sum of the values of snmpFddiSMTNonMasterCt and snmpFddiSMTMasterCt on the given SMT.

cntFddiPORTMaintLineState.name: cntFddiPORTMaintLineState
cntFddiPORTMaintLineState.description: The current maintenance line status of this PORT.

cntFddiPORTEBErrs.name: cntFddiPORTEBErrs
cntFddiPORTEBErrs.description: The count of the times an Elasticity Buffer Error has occurred.

cntFddiPORTBaseLerEstimate.name: cntFddiPORTBaseLerEstimate
cntFddiPORTBaseLerEstimate.description: The value of FddiPORTLerEstimate at the sample time prior to when the sample time that the PORT LER Event was generated (the condition became active).

cntFddiPORTBaseLemRejects.name: cntFddiPORTBaseLemRejects
cntFddiPORTBaseLemRejects.description: The value of FddiPORTLerRejectCt at the sample time prior to when the sample time that the PORT LER Event was generated (the condition became active).

cntFddiPORTBaseLems.name: cntFddiPORTBaseLems
cntFddiPORTBaseLems.description: The value of FddiPORTLerCt at the sample time prior to when the sample time that the PORT LER Event was generated (the condition became active).

cntFddiPORTBaseLerTimeStamp.name: cntFddiPORTBaseLerTimeStamp
cntFddiPORTBaseLerTimeStamp.description: The value of FddiSMTMsgTimestamp at the sample time prior to when the sample time that the PORT LER Event was generated (the condition became active).

cntMibVersion.name: cntMibVersion
cntMibVersion.description: The version identifier of the mib file that the agent has loaded from BBRAM.

cntMibObjectCount.name: cntMibObjectCount
cntMibObjectCount.description: Number of objects in the MIB description file, !MIB, in this CNT platform. This file contains objects from RFC 1213, RFC 1284, RFC 1285, and CNT's enterprise. Depending upon the configuration of this node, the node may or may not support all of these objects.

cntConfigVersion.name: cntConfigVersion
cntConfigVersion.description: Version number of this SNMP agent from the configuration record.

cntProxyStatus.name: cntProxyStatus
cntProxyStatus.description: This flag indicates whether this SNMP agent is acting as a proxy, is being proxied, or is a normally behaving SNMP agent.

cntProxyCount.name: cntProxyCount
cntProxyCount.description: If this node is configured to operate as a proxy agent, this number reflects the number of proxied nodes that this node is configured to manage in !NDE.

cntSnmpBufferCount.name: cntSnmpBufferCount
cntSnmpBufferCount.description: Number of buffers reserved for this SNMP agent for outgoing message from the configuration record.

cntIfPollInterval.name: cntIfPollInterval
cntIfPollInterval.description: Number of seconds for the SNMP agent to wait between checks of the CNT platform's interfaces for operation status. These interface checks result in the link down and link up traps. This value is from the configuration record.

cntIfNextPoll.name: cntIfNextPoll
cntIfNextPoll.description: Number of seconds for the next internal SNMP agent interface poll. These interface checks result in the link down and link up traps. This value is from the configuration record.

cntDoDIPCount.name: cntDoDIPCount
cntDoDIPCount.description: The number of DoD IP addresses (internet records in !CFG) configured in this node that the agent detected upon startup. This will not equal the number of interfaces on this node.

cntDot3Count.name: cntDot3Count
cntDot3Count.description: The number of ethernet interfaces that are manageable by this agent on this node.

cntFddiCount.name: cntFddiCount
cntFddiCount.description: The number of FDDI interfaces that are manageable by this agent on this node.

cntFddiPortCount.name: cntFddiPortCount
cntFddiPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports that are manageable by this agent on this node.

cntDataLinkCount.name: cntDataLinkCount
cntDataLinkCount.description: The number of Data Link Layers Instances that are manageable by this agent on this node.

cntLLC1Count.name: cntLLC1Count
cntLLC1Count.description: The number of Data Link Layers Instances of type Logical Link Control 1 (ISO 8802/2) that are manageable by this agent on this node.

cntCofiVersion.name: cntCofiVersion
cntCofiVersion.description: The version of the the COmmon File Interface (COFI) module that is loaded into this node. COFI is required by the snmp agent for access to some CNT system objects. The version is in the format: version.day.month.year.

cntMib2Requests.name: cntMib2Requests
cntMib2Requests.description: The number of requests received by the agent for mib-2 objects.

cntFddiRequests.name: cntFddiRequests
cntFddiRequests.description: The number of requests received by the agent for FDDI objects in the experimental or transmission subtree.

cntDot3Requests.name: cntDot3Requests
cntDot3Requests.description: The number of requests received by the agent for 802.3 objects in the experimental or transmission subtree.

cntCntRequests.name: cntCntRequests
cntCntRequests.description: The number of requests received by the agent for objects in the Computer Network Technology Corp. private enterprise subtree.

cntRowAdditions.name: cntRowAdditions
cntRowAdditions.description: The number of table row additions that have been successful through SNMP requests from a network management station.

cntRowModifies.name: cntRowModifies
cntRowModifies.description: The number of table row modifications that have been successful through SNMP requests from a network management station.

cntRowDeletions.name: cntRowDeletions
cntRowDeletions.description: The number of table row deletions that have been successful through SNMP requests from a network management station.

cntRowErrors.name: cntRowErrors
cntRowErrors.description: The number of table row additions that were attempted through SNMP requests from a network management station, but were not complete in a single request. These requests were not successfully completed.

cntBadVersions.name: cntBadVersions
cntBadVersions.description: The number of table row additions that were attempted through SNMP requests from a network management station, but were not complete in a single request. These requests were not successfully completed.

cntNoBuffers.name: cntNoBuffers
cntNoBuffers.description: The number of times the agent needed a buffer and did not have one. The agent uses buffers when making requests to the MEs.

cntMailTimeouts.name: cntMailTimeouts
cntMailTimeouts.description: The number of timeouts received from the MEs when a mib request was given.

cntCachedResponses.name: cntCachedResponses
cntCachedResponses.description: The number of requests to the MEs that were cached. Each cached message contains as many mib objects as the request to the ME.

cntUsedCaches.name: cntUsedCaches
cntUsedCaches.description: The number of objects for which the cached mib objects were used.

cntTrapDestCount.name: cntTrapDestCount
cntTrapDestCount.description: The number of trap destinations that the agent will forward the configured traps to.

cntLastTrapMsg.name: cntLastTrapMsg
cntLastTrapMsg.description: Textual description of the last trap message sent from this SNMP agent. The object identifier for cntSysLastTrapMsg is sent along with each trap.

cntTrapTable.name: cntTrapTable
cntTrapTable.description: A list of trap entries. There is a maximum of six trap entries. These values, except TrapIf, are set in the configuration record.

cnttrapEntry.name: cnttrapEntry
cnttrapEntry.description: A trap entry containing the information needed to send out a trap.

cntsnmpTrapFlags.name: cntsnmpTrapFlags
cntsnmpTrapFlags.description: Flag setting specifying which types of traps to send to this destination. This value is derived from 'or'ing the following values: cold start(0x01), link down(0x04), link up(0x08), and authentication failure(0x10).

cntTrapFlags.name: cntTrapFlags
cntTrapFlags.description: Flag settings reserved for future enterprise specific trap enabling.

cntProxyTable.name: cntProxyTable
cntProxyTable.description: A list of proxy entries. This table contains an entry for each proxied node from this proxy agent. If this node is not configured as a proxy agent then this table is empty.

cntproxyEntry.name: cntproxyEntry
cntproxyEntry.description: A proxy entry containing the information needed to carry an SNMP request to a proxied node.

cntproxyAddress.name: cntproxyAddress
cntproxyAddress.description: Proxied node destination DoD IP address that is used by the NMS.

cntproxyNode.name: cntproxyNode
cntproxyNode.description: Proxied node destination CNT node address that is used by the local CNT router to access the destination.

cntTraceTable.name: cntTraceTable
cntTraceTable.description: List of entries in the global trace area.

cnttraceIndex.name: cnttraceIndex
cnttraceIndex.description: The index which uniquely identifies the trace row instance in a CNT node.

cnttraceCpu.name: cnttraceCpu
cnttraceCpu.description: The CPU number of the module that entered this trace entry.

cnttraceData.name: cnttraceData
cnttraceData.description: The remaining 14 octets of trace information.

cntMDMTable.name: cntMDMTable
cntMDMTable.description: A list of Message Distribution Manager (MDM) interprocessor queue global table entries.

cntMDMEntry.name: cntMDMEntry
cntMDMEntry.description: A Message Distribution Manager (MDM) queue global table entry.

cntmdmQIndex.name: cntmdmQIndex
cntmdmQIndex.description: The relative index of the MDM entry in the system's global table.

cntmdmQName.name: cntmdmQName
cntmdmQName.description: The MDM queue name for this entry in the system global table.

cntmdmQProcessId.name: cntmdmQProcessId
cntmdmQProcessId.description: The MDM processor number for this entry in the system global table.

cntmdmQTaskId.name: cntmdmQTaskId
cntmdmQTaskId.description: The MDM task identifier for this entry in the system global table.

cntmdmQList.name: cntmdmQList
cntmdmQList.description: The MDM queue name list in one long string.

cntdlNumber.name: cntdlNumber
cntdlNumber.description: The number of network data link layers present on this system.

cntdlTable.name: cntdlTable
cntdlTable.description: A list of data link layer entries. The number of entries is given by the value of cntdlNumber.

cntdlEntry.name: cntdlEntry
cntdlEntry.description: A data link layer entry containing objects for a particular data link layer.

cntdlIndex.name: cntdlIndex
cntdlIndex.description: A unique value for each data link layer. It's value ranges between one and the value of dlNumber. The value for each data link layer must remain constant at least from one reinitialization of the entity's network management system to the next reinitialization.

cntdlDescr.name: cntdlDescr
cntdlDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the data link layer. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the data link layer.

cntdlType.name: cntdlType
cntdlType.description: The type of this data link layer.

cntdlTypeofService.name: cntdlTypeofService
cntdlTypeofService.description: The type of this data link layer service.

cntdlMtu.name: cntdlMtu
cntdlMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on this data link layer, specified in octets.

cntdlPortAddrLen.name: cntdlPortAddrLen
cntdlPortAddrLen.description: The length of all port addresses used by this data link layer service.

cntdlMaxPort.name: cntdlMaxPort
cntdlMaxPort.description: The maximum number of ports supported by this data link layer service.

cntdlActivePort.name: cntdlActivePort
cntdlActivePort.description: The current number of active ports.

cntdlInOctets.name: cntdlInOctets
cntdlInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this data link layer.

cntdlInUcastPkts.name: cntdlInUcastPkts
cntdlInUcastPkts.description: The number of unicast packets delivered to a higher layer protocol.

cntdlInNUcastPkts.name: cntdlInNUcastPkts
cntdlInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast packets delivered to a higher layer protocol.

cntdlInDiscards.name: cntdlInDiscards
cntdlInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher layer protocol.

cntdlInErrors.name: cntdlInErrors
cntdlInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

cntdlInUnknownProtos.name: cntdlInUnknownProtos
cntdlInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the data link layer which were discareded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

cntdlOutOctets.name: cntdlOutOctets
cntdlOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted by this this data link layer service.

cntdlOutUcastPkts.name: cntdlOutUcastPkts
cntdlOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cntdlOutNUcastPkts.name: cntdlOutNUcastPkts
cntdlOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cntdlOutDiscards.name: cntdlOutDiscards
cntdlOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chose to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted.

cntdlOutErrors.name: cntdlOutErrors
cntdlOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

cntdlOutQLen.name: cntdlOutQLen
cntdlOutQLen.description: The length of the output packet queue, in packets.

cntdlPortTable.name: cntdlPortTable
cntdlPortTable.description: A list of data link layer entries. The number of entries is given by the value of dlActivePorts.

cntdlPortEntry.name: cntdlPortEntry
cntdlPortEntry.description: A data link layer entry containing objects for a particular port.

cntdlPortType.name: cntdlPortType
cntdlPortType.description: The port type. This value is not redundant to dlType since a link layer service may support multiple port types. For example, LLC1 has both llc1 and snap ports.

cntllc1ConfigTable.name: cntllc1ConfigTable
cntllc1ConfigTable.description: A list of the LLC1 configuration entries.

cntllc1ConfigIndex.name: cntllc1ConfigIndex
cntllc1ConfigIndex.description: The index that uniquely identifies an instance of a LLC1 process in a CNT node.

cntllc1DriverType.name: cntllc1DriverType
cntllc1DriverType.description: The physical layer device driver type that has identified to this llc1 service.

cntllc1Addr.name: cntllc1Addr
cntllc1Addr.description: The MAC address for the physical layer over which this link layer is operating.

cntllc1InitFlag.name: cntllc1InitFlag
cntllc1InitFlag.description: The initialization flag indicating whether or not this module has finished initializing the data link layer stack.

cntllc1TraceFlag.name: cntllc1TraceFlag
cntllc1TraceFlag.description: The trace flags in bit-oriented form. The values are as follows: .... ...1 - phase 2 entry point .... ..1. - phase 3 entry point .... .1.. - messages in .... 1... - transmit completions ...1 .... - messages received ..1. .... - message to a ULP.

cntllc1BufCnt.name: cntllc1BufCnt
cntllc1BufCnt.description: The number of free buffers in the free pool.

cntllc1BusId.name: cntllc1BusId
cntllc1BusId.description: The bus number for this network interface.

cntllc1CpuNum.name: cntllc1CpuNum
cntllc1CpuNum.description: The CPU number where this data link layer is running, 1 through 8.

cntllc1BufPriority.name: cntllc1BufPriority
cntllc1BufPriority.description: The assigned buffer priority for messages received from the physical layer.

cntllc1WaitTimeOut.name: cntllc1WaitTimeOut
cntllc1WaitTimeOut.description: The wait timeout in seconds for XID/TEST frames sent to a peer llc1 data link layer.

cntllc1StatsTable.name: cntllc1StatsTable
cntllc1StatsTable.description: A list of LLC1 statistics entries.

cntllc1StatIndex.name: cntllc1StatIndex
cntllc1StatIndex.description: The index that uniquely identifies an instance of a LLC1 process in a CNT node.

cntllc1InXids.name: cntllc1InXids
cntllc1InXids.description: The number of LLC XID frames received from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InTests.name: cntllc1InTests
cntllc1InTests.description: The number of LLC TEST frames received from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InUIs.name: cntllc1InUIs
cntllc1InUIs.description: The number of LLC UI frames received from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InNoDsaps.name: cntllc1InNoDsaps
cntllc1InNoDsaps.description: The number of unknown DSAPs received from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InXidOks.name: cntllc1InXidOks
cntllc1InXidOks.description: The number of successful LLC XID frames from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InTestOks.name: cntllc1InTestOks
cntllc1InTestOks.description: The number of successful LLC TEST frames from a peer data link layer.

cntllc1InSnapIps.name: cntllc1InSnapIps
